CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 18, 1950, pg. 10, reads: "AT THE YWCA DINNER... last Thursday night these interesting women were seated at the head table, overlooking the crowded Soldiers and Sailors Memorial Hall, where scores of guests enjoyed the annual pot-luck dinner. Left to right: Mrs. W. R. Viyrett, Mrs. S. E. Eliot, Mrs. Harold S. Metcalfe, Mrs. George L. West, Miss Anne Guthrie, the dynamic speaker; Mrs. William Cuthbert, Mrs. Robert D. Campbell, Mrs. C. L. Mellon and Mrs. Goldie D. Carter. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Speaker Anne Guthrie standing behind microphone at banquet table for YWCA dinner at Soldiers and Sailors Memorial Hall, Oakland
